My current version of OpenSSH :

* OpenSSH_6.0p1-hpn13v11, OpenSSL 1.0.1c 10 May 2012

And generating a key with

{{{\\
ssh-keygen -t ecdsa -b 521\\
}}}

Generates a public key with the following leading:

{{{\\
ecdsa-sha2-nistp521\\
}}}

However, the sites public key submission field rejects my public key regardless of what I do

I changed name of my repository to https://bitbucket.org/gkt/variable-length-video-prefix-caching. After that I am unable to push to it.\\
{{{\\
#!shell

git push -u git@bitbucket.org:gkt/variable-length-video-prefix-caching.git master\\
ssh: connect to host bitbucket.org port 22: Connection timed out\\
fatal: The remote end hung up unexpectedly

}}}

For viewing a news (on dashboard) about a commit (from not existing bitbucket-user) his avatar leads to page:

{{bitbucket.org/firstName lastName}}

and there, naturally, is error 404.
